  "prompt": "Why do gel nails get stained? How do you prevent this from happening?",
  "response": "Gel nails can get stained for several reasons, primarily due to exposure to pigmented substances or certain environmental factors. Here are the main causes and prevention tips:\n\n### **Why Gel Nails Get Stained:**\n1. **Pigmented Products:**\n   - Nail polishes (especially dark or highly pigmented colors), dyes, or inks can seep into the top layer of the gel.\n   - Hair dyes, henna, or fabric dyes can also cause stains.\n\n2. **Everyday Substances:**\n   - Foods and beverages with strong colorants (e.g., coffee, tea, turmeric, berries, or tomato sauce) can discolor gel nails.\n   - Smoking can cause yellowing or browning of nails.\n\n3. **Chemical Exposure:**\n   - Cleaning products, chlorine (in swimming pools), or harsh chemicals can react with the gel and cause discoloration.\n\n4. **Improper Curing:**\n   - If the gel polish is not fully cured under the UV/LED lamp, it may remain porous and more susceptible to staining.\n\n5. **Top Coat Issues:**\n   - A worn-out or damaged top coat can make the nails more vulnerable to staining.\n\n### **How to Prevent Gel Nail Stains:**\n1. **Use a Base Coat:**\n   - Always apply a high-quality base coat before the gel polish to create a barrier between the nail and pigmented products.\n\n2. **Fully Cure the Gel:**\n   - Ensure that the gel polish is properly cured under the UV/LED lamp for the recommended time to avoid porosity.\n\n3. **Apply a Quality Top Coat:**\n   - Use a durable top coat to seal the color and protect it from external factors.\n\n4. **Wear Gloves:**\n   - Protect your nails by wearing gloves when using cleaning products, handling hair dyes, or working with staining substances.\n\n5. **Quick Clean-Up:**\n   - If your nails come into contact with staining substances, clean them immediately with water and soap.\n\n6. **Avoid Prolonged Exposure:**\n   - Minimize contact with highly pigmented foods, beverages, or other staining agents.\n\n7. **Choose Lighter Colors:**\n   - Darker gel polishes are more prone to staining, so consider lighter shades if staining is a recurring issue.\n\n8. **Regular Maintenance:**\n   - Keep your nails well-maintained by reapplying the top coat as needed to maintain its protective layer.\n\nBy following these tips, you can significantly reduce the likelihood of your gel nails getting stained and keep them looking fresh and vibrant.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
